# Gogo Testing, Deployment, And Upgrade Rules

Use this rule when adding tests, changing commands, deploying, upgrading Gogo,
or verifying production readiness.

Framework module: `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo`.

## Testing

- Add focused tests for changed behavior.
- Run app/package tests before broad project tests.
- Use Gogo testing helpers for HTTP clients, settings, databases, fixtures,
  mail, queues, admin assertions, and framework behavior.
- Keep tests independent of production services unless explicitly marked as
  integration coverage.

## Common Commands

```bash
make test
make check
make tidy
gogo check
```

For generated project or deployment changes, also run:

```bash
gogo check --deploy
```

## External Integrations

- PostgreSQL integration requires a database URL.
- Redis integration requires Redis connection settings.
- RabbitMQ integration requires RabbitMQ connection settings.
- Report which external integrations were not exercised when verification
  skips them.

## Deployment

- Run web, worker, and beat from the same project version.
- Apply migrations before serving code that depends on new schema.
- Collect static files before deploying static asset changes.
- Keep old application versions available until migrations, workers, beat, and
  smoke tests are verified.

## Upgrades

- Pin `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo` in `go.mod`.
- Read Gogo `CHANGELOG.md` before upgrading.
- Verify generated project behavior after dependency updates.
- Confirm `gogo version` matches the intended framework version.
